Reasoning: The paper discusses the effect of visual design on classification tasks, specifically using two data sets - one with spatial dependencies and one with financial data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of visual representations in decision-making, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also mentions supervised classification, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The use of visual design to guard against overfitting and introduce new features suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the mention of financial data suggests that the paper could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
